ore Christmas - just how are supply issues and shortages affecting bookshops...</div></div></div></div><div class="aos-CarouselSlide aos-FL aos-W100 aos-H100 aos-DFSW"><div class="aos-OFH aos-FL aos-W100 aos-H100 aos-DFSW"><div class="aos-carousel-img aos-PosR aos-OFH aos-DF aos-DFW aos-TAC aos-MBXS"><a href="https://www.thebookseller.com/blogs/publishers-must-help-bookshops-bounce-back-1262119" ><img loading="lazy" src="https&#x3a;&#x2f;&#x2f;drsw10gc90t0z.cloudfront.net&#x2f;AcuCustom&#x2f;Sitename&#x2f;DAM&#x2f;121&#x2f;Unknown-removebg_Thumb.png" alt="Publishers&#x20;must&#x20;help&#x20;bookshops&#x20;bounce&#x20;back" title="Publishers&#x20;must&#x20;help&#x20;bookshops&#x20;bounce&#x20;back" class="aos-ArticleImage aos-Image" /></a></div><div class="aos-ArticleTextContainer aos-OFH aos-DynWidth aos-FL aos-W100"><h2 class="aos-ArticleTitle aos-DS33-H2 aos-FL100 aos-M0 aos-DF aos-TAL aos-MB5px"><a href="https://www.thebookseller.com/blogs/publishers-must-help-bookshops-bounce-back-1262119" >Publishers must help bookshops bounce back</a></h2><div class="aos-ArticleMetaData aos-DS33-MData aos-W100 aos-FL aos-DF aos-DFW aos-TAL"><span class="aos-ArticleAuthor aos-NM aos-FL aos-MB5px aos-DF">by&nbsp;Joseph Evans</span></div><div class="aos-DS33-Teaser">The pandemic altered where readers bought books and the types of titles they purchased&#8212;and it&#8217;s time publishers used their profits to help bookshops out.</div></div></div></div></div><div id="aos-carousel-dots2722" class="aos-carousel-dots owl-dots aos-MT20px"></div></div>
